<content-text><p><b>Lab Activity</b></p> <p>Use the knowledge and skills presented in this course to perform the following tasks:</p> <p><ul><li> Analyze a network design and create a hierarchical addressing scheme.</li><li> Configure switches with multiple VLANs, VTP, and port security.</li><li> Configure routers and switches to allow inter-VLAN routing.</li><li> Configure multiple routers using OSPF, PAT, a default route, and route summarization.</li><li> Configure WAN links using PPP and authentication.</li><li> Configure ACLs to control network access and to secure routers.</li><li> Verify connectivity, device configuration, and functionality. </li></ul></p><p><b>Click the lab icon to begin.</b></p></content-text>
</page>
